name: The Shops at Columbus Circle
directions: 2nd Floor
comment: Clean. Easy. Across from Central Park.

name: North Station
directions: Inside North Station at the Commuter rail station, around the corner from the McDonalds/Dunkin'Donuts by the TD Garden Pro Shop.
comment: Not many people realize this bathroom is here!!!

name: Walla Walla Regional Airport
directions: Family restroom; near the men's and women's rooms and the gift shop

name: Orange County Airport
directions: Family bathroom located between the men's and women's rooms.Located inside the 'secure' area of the terminal, so you must have a valid boarding pass.

name: Cal Anderson Park
directions: Just north of the playfields.  It's a public restroom- no need to bother the shop owners in the neighborhood!
comment: Great tacos across the street.

name: Dado Tea
directions: In a long hallway behind Dado.
comment: You have to ask at the counter for the Bathroom Key, which they will only give if you purchase something, but they have many inexpensive (and tasty!) items for sale.

name: Lowes
directions: Off I-79
comment: Lowes has a mens room, women's room and an actual unisex bathroom!  I was amazed and always try to shop there now.

name: Floyd's Coffee
directions: Just past the counter, through a door on the left.

name: Cosmic Cafe
directions: Inside the cafe, to the right (but straight ahead/down the hall) of the register (NOT up the stairs!).
comment: Small, single person lockable toilet. No urinal.Ironically, a sign in the men's room warns you to avoid alcohol \"If you are pregnant or think you may be pregnant\". Just in case, guys!

name: Cafe Brazil
directions: Straight ahead of the front entry, women\\'s is to the right and down the hall. MUST be a paying customer, they are strict about this.
comment: Small, single person, lockable toilet. Men\\'s is usually well-kept.

name: Cafe Brazil
directions: Bathrooms are to the left of the counter/bar, to the right of the coffee station. The bathrooms are large, lockable, and usually well-kept. Men's room has both toilet and urinal.
comment: This Cafe Brazil is pretty queer-friendly and located near SMU so it is usually well populated by college kids. The coffee is great, parking is terrible!

name: j c penneys
directions: Hwy 71 exit gemini parkway and go west to mall, JC Penneys is on the left.  Family bathroom converted to Unisex bathroom, accessable.  First floor, back by catalog.  Just ask where restrooms are, it is next to them!

name: First UU Church of Youngstown OH
directions: Accessible bathroom on lower floor end of hall, small unisex on upper floor by office.

name: New Moon Bar
directions: Behind bar

name: Exxon
directions: back left of store in small hallway.
comment: Small Stall.  24 hours.

name: WalMart
directions: All the way in the back of the store in the restrooms area.  Go towards the shoe section.  'Family Restroom'
comment: I believe it is open 24 hours.  The WalMart on 4th street is gendered.

name: University of Minnesota Duluth
directions: The two unisex bathrooms at UMD are on the first floor of campus. You walk to the area around the ITSS room (the computer repair shop), and then walk into the Montague hallway on the first floor. There will be two single-occupancy locking restroom stalls to the right side.
comment: A lot of people like to use these bathrooms during passing time (between classes), so it will be to your advantage to *not* go between xx:50 and xx:00 as these are passing times.

name: Telluride Gondola Station
directions: Entrance is on the SE facing wall, or to your left if you are facing the gondola entrance
comment: public.  There are several other public restrooms in telluride

name: Northwestern University
directions: This is on the first floor of Lunt Hall.  Once you walk in and go up 5 or so steps, it's in the big main hall.
comment: It's probably only available to Northwestern University students.It's a single locking room and has a men/women/handicap accessible sign on it.

name: First Unitarian Church of Oakland
directions: On the first floor there are gendered restrooms that are designated with a sign as safe for Transgender. On the 2nd and 3rd floors there are single stall restrooms.
comment: The church is not alweays open during the week, but on Sundays or if you are attending an event a very safe place to pee!

name: Unitarian Universalist Congregation of Grand Traverse
directions: Inside the front door, the bathroom is to the left just before the church office.
comment: We are a Welcoming Congregation, open to all gender and sexual identities.

name: West Shore Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: There are three unisex/family bathrooms.  Enter from the parking lot entrance (east entrance).  The most commonly used by the public are directly forward through the rotunda.  Take the first hallway on your left that does not have a door.  Turn left again and there are two bathrooms right there.  There is a unisex bathroom to your right and all the way down the small hallway.
comment: This is a church and is open 8AM to 10PM Monday through Friday, most Saturdays during the day, and during the morning and afternoon on Sundays.The 2009-10 intern minister is/was genderqueer and the congregation is a welcoming congregation to the GLBT community.

name: Woods Supermarket
directions: Located to the left of the pharmacy

name: Drunken Monkey
comment: ÁMonday - Thursday, 7am to 10pm.ÁFriday 7am to midnight.ÁSaturday 8am to midnight.ÁSunday 9am to 10pm.

name: Century 21 Department Store
directions: In Regular store you go down stairs or elevator to the left wall or in homestore you go straight right to back.
comment: Plenty of clean bathroom stalls. Separate bathrooms for male and female. Cleanest bathrooms in Bay Ridge...Wheelchair accesibile.

name: George's Route 66 Bar & Grill
directions: Phone for directions: 314-961-1119
comment: Regularly on Wednesdays I see a few transgendered customers there dancing and having a great time and they use the women's restroom...never bothered. It's a good crowd, everyone just there to be themselves. Very low key atmosphere.

name: Coburg Coffee House
directions: Single-stall washroom located in the back of the cafe to the left.Accessible entrance at rear of the building.
comment: Open Daily 7am - 9pmTuesdays 7am - 10pmCoburg offers a variety of hot and cold drinks, including fair trade organic coffee, plus a selection of sandwiches, salads, sweets, and a daily soup. Can't beat their London Fog (especially if you ask for extra vanilla).Free wifi (password is posted).An added feature is the Coburg Book Exchange. Pick up something to read while you're there and drop off your used books for others to enjoy.

name: good food emporium
directions: back right corner of the restaurant
comment: Hours: Mon/Tue 7am-6pm; Wed-Fri 7am-9pm; Sat/Sun 10am-2pm

name: the trident
directions: just walk to the back left corner of the first room in the cafe (behind all the book shelves)
comment: hours:mon-fri 8am-5:30pmsat:8:30am-5pmsun: 10am-5pm

name: minato sushi
directions: back left corner
comment: Hours: Monday and Tuesday, 11:00am to 9:00pm Wednesday, 4:30pm to 9:00pm Thursday to Saturday, 11:30am to 9:00pm

name: anchor archive
comment: Open hours : Sunday 2-5pm and Tuesday 6-9pm902-446-1788

name: Just Us!
comment: Monday through Friday7:30am - 9pmSaturday8am - 6pmSunday9am - 6pm(902) 423-0856

name: Clay cafe
directions: wheelchair ramp to front door. back left corner of the cafe.

name: youth project
comment: not always open.call beforehand (902) gay-5-gay this is also a queer youth centre for youth 25 and under. there is a food bank here as well.

name: java blend
directions: walk in.to the right of the counter is a door. walk through this door and at the back right corner of that coffee roasting room in the bathroom.you can probably just ask to use it and they will let you.ADD: The journey to this bathroom is a quintessential Halifax experience.  Follow the silver line like Alice in Wonderland and soak in the coffee aroma en route.
comment: Tel: (902) 423-6944 (local)Toll Free: 1-877-596-JAVA (5282)Email: info@javablendcoffee.comHours of Service:Monday to Friday, 6.30am to 6pmSaturday, 8am to 5pm(Atlantic Standard Time)

name: Starbucks
directions: Back of store. M-Su 5am-9:30pm.
comment: Single stall toilet, no urinal. Use like a public restroom...everyone else does (just be clean about it!).

name: Glazers Coffee
directions: Back of store
comment: M-Th 6:30am-9pm, Fr 6:30-10pm Sa-Su 9am-10pm. Probably be cool with just going in to pee, but since it's an awesome place with nice baristas, buying something would be really nice.

name: Emerson College (Piano Row Residence Hall)
directions: first floor at the end of the hallway
comment: during the day during the college operating semester you are free to stroll back there to use the bathroom, except during the night and the weekend.

name: Sidney Borum Health Center
directions: LGBTQ friendly doctor office. you have to be buzzed in first though.
comment: LGBTQ friendly doctor office. you have to be buzzed in first though.

name: Emerson College Library
directions: 3rd floorduring the weekday, between 9-5 you can stroll right into the building without being carded

name: Woodson & Associates
street: 183 West State Street / Route 202, Suite C
directions: Enter through Woodson & Associates (Suite C) and the friendly person at the desk will direct you.

name: SUNY Cortland
directions: They have single rooms with private baths to accomadate TG students. Check with Student Disability Services and housing. Must have a Doctor or Mental Health professional's letter stating you are TG. There are no 'pulic' bathrooms that are nuatral anywhere else on campus, but they are working on that. Also, to access the pool at al, you must go through either the mens or ladies lockerrooms.
comment: The college and I have just started a Gender Idenitity and Expression Committee to address the needs of TG students and employees. Thier mission includes enforcing non-discrimination policy, person-first language, and the dreaded bathroom/shower/lockerroom issues. The committee is made up of students, RA's, Staff, administratio, and community members. I am the only TG student on campus and in the committee as of this date.

name: Corning Community College
directions: 3 labeled 'Man/Woman/Handicapped' in cafeteria building. One on first floor, two in lower floor by Student Disability Services office. One on 3rd floor of Nursing building, not handicapped accessible. They have planned for gender nuetral baths, showers, and lockers in thier new Gym biulding, in the 5-year plan.
comment: I made these changes with some supportive professors and the Dean of Students when I attended college there. CCC is a very small Jr. College with fewer than 2,000 students (No dorms). But they have made these simple changes in a small town and no budget! Vivats to CCC. If they can do it, any college can!

name: NEW Super Walmart
directions: Go to the restroom at back of store along back wall
comment: \"Family Use\" Sign. Has toilet, urinal, and a mini-potty for youngsters in one large room. Also changing table

name: Wright Food Court
directions: On the north and south sides of the eating areas there are gender neutral, single stall, locking restrooms.
comment: Open whenever the building is.  Card swipe access may be necessary after midnight.

name: Gresham Food Court
directions: There is one on each side of the main doors into the building.
comment: They are both labeled as Gender Neutral and are single stall locking facilities.  They are also the only public bathrooms in the building. They are open whenever the building is (7am-Midnight?)

name: University of California San Diego LGBT Resource Center
directions: The LGBT Resource Center is located in the Student Center in the middle of campus. There is one bathroom downstairs below the Center, and one located inside the Center.
comment: These bathrooms are specifically gender-neutral and open to anyone on campus, no questions asked.

name: Walmart
directions: At the front of the store between the two entrances
comment: 24 hours

name: Kohl's
directions: Near Customer service
comment: There is a Male bathroom, Female bathroom and a Unisex bathroom

name: Ross Dress for Less
directions: Go to the back of the store where the fitting counter is.
comment: They may stop you to see if you have any unpaid for items (Because the bathroom is right inbetween two of the fitting rooms, and the counter is there for that reason.) Only one bathroom available. The building is old and the owners (Ross rents the building) refuse to remodel it, so it may not look clean.

name: St Cloud State University
directions: Second floor of Atwood Memorial near the LGBT resource center. Two separate locking door restrooms.

name: Sprague Memorial Library, Harvey Mudd College
directions: There is a card swipe entrance on the far west wall. There are bathrooms on each floor in the southwest corner.1st + 4th floor: 1 'mens' and one 'women's' restroom, single stall and locking.2nd floor: Unknown3rd floor: 1 unisex bathroom, with a menstrual product dispenser.5th floor: 1 unisex bathroom with a urinal.
comment: The hours of this building are very unreliable, since it is currently being renovated.Beware that the elevator may be disabled for certain floors, card access may be required to enter certain floors through the stairwell, and some doors may sound alarms when opened. Beware!

name: Southernmost Beach Cafe
directions: Near the beach bar

name: Parsons Engineering Building, Harvey Mudd College
directions: There are two bathrooms on the first floor, one in the east-most and one in the west-most hallway.
comment: Open whenever school is open. (9-5 Mon-Fri; occasionally at other times)

name: Richardson Dance Studio, Scripps College
directions: There are two gendered single stall locking bathrooms on the east side of the studio.The door labeled 'men' is inside a male dressing room, so it might not be as useful. However, the entrance to the bathroom labeled 'women' is not in a gendered space.
comment: Expect them to be open M-F 9-5 or when classes are in session.

name: Valhalla
directions: The bathrooms are in the back of the bar!  They are generally pretty clean and have lots of space.
comment: Valhalla is a really nice beer bar with a lot of taps and heavily rotating selection.  1 Men's room, 1 Women's room.  Each bathroom is a single room with a locking door.

name: Downtown Historic Branson
directions: Located in the parking lot behind Dicks 5 & 10.  North Commercial Street (turn north at the 4-way stop in Historic Down-Town Branson, one block and it is on the left.
comment: This facility is run by the city of Branson and it is clean and safe. I am not certain about the days and hours that it is open, but you can call the City of Branson at (417) 334-3345 and ask if you are planning a visit.

name: ROTC Houses, SIUC
directions: Back building has one unisex restroom.  The front building has two, one on each floor

name: Yogurtland
directions: Near the back entrance. You can't miss it.
comment: Company website and hours: http://www.yogurt-land.com/ .

name: Firefly Bistro
comment: Restaurant website and hours: http://www.eatatfirefly.com/index2.html .

name: Manhattan Bar
directions: Straight to the back on the left. Two locking stalls.
comment: This is a bar so it's open during nighttime hours. Free for 21's and up.

name: Darby's Cafe
comment: You don't really have to flirt - just ask.

name: Mrs. Grossman's Sticker Factory
directions: Walk in the fron door towards the stairs and hook a left. Restrooms are right there.
comment: Great place to do a little sticker shopping afterwards in the shop upstairs, or arrange to take the tour. Great prices & huge selection.

name: Dockside Park
comment: There are showers in here, too.

name: Olympia Farmers Market
directions: At the North end of the Farmers Market near the parking lot.
comment: Only open Thursday - Sunday when the market is open.

name: 13th Note Cafe
directions: walk towards restaurant area at back, turn right, disabled toilet on right.
comment: Very nice trans friendly place to have tea, free wifi etc

name: I-75 NB Rest Area at MM 413
directions: In center of building, between the men's wing and the women's wing.
comment: Slight lip at the door, which is relatively light for being made of metal. The lock is another of those stubby little keys that turn a deadbolt, but requires only a 45-degree turn and little force.

name: Brooklyn Public Library
directions: The bathrooms is located near by the meeting room.
comment: Anyone can use the bathrooms. Just ask for a key before you use the bathroom. Both bathrooms consist of a locking door for men and women. Closed on Sundays.

name: Olympia Food Co-op (Eastside Location)
directions: Two bathrooms, both accessible. Go to the right after entering the store. One is past the fruit cooler on the right, the other is through the warehouse entryway, immediately to the left.

name: Olympia Food Co-op (Westside Location)
directions: Two bathrooms in the warehouse (storage section of the store.) One is large and accessible, the other is not.
comment: Co-op is open seven days a week (except for New Years Day) from 8 AM to 9 PM.

name: Vics Pizza
directions: The bathroom is in the back, past the bar and the water fountain. It's currently not very accessible to those in wheel chairs, but a new bathroom was being built last week, and it might be accessible.

name: Wicked Grounds
directions: Through the archway!
comment: We are a kink cafe, so are totally open and welcoming to ALL, regardless of however you define yourself!You probably should buy something, but if you ask the staff nicely, we are totally understanding of individual situations and will let you use the bathroom!

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Ask for the code. It's in the back, next to the parking lot.

name: Sacred Grounds Cafe
directions: Behind the counter
comment: Graffiti-tastic, too.

name: Atmospheric Sciences Building
directions: Use the sidewalk-level entrance in the southwest corner of the building. Walk straight past the elevator and turn right; it will be in the corner to your right.
comment: Locking, genderfree bathroom with urinal and stall. Stall might be kind of small for a wheelchair. Building is open 8AM-5PM on weekdays only.

name: Tap and Mallet
directions: the bathrooms are in the back; from the front door, walk toward the back left
comment: its a restaurant/bar...open Mon-Sat 11:30am-2am; Sun 4pm-12am

name: Scripps College Seal Court
directions: On the SE side of Seal Court

name: Scripps College Sallie Tiernan Fieldhouse
directions: 2 genderfree, accessible restrooms on both the 1st and 2nd floor (4 total). First floor: to the right of the front desk. Second floor: at the back of room 201. Elevator is on the N side of the building. Downstairs there are gendered locker-rooms which are accessible.
comment: Hours can be found here: http://www.scrippscollege.edu/campus/tiernan-field-house/hours-of-operation.php

name: Scripps College Malott Commons
directions: On the west side of the building, downstairs, down the hall past the meeting rooms, to the left through two doors, next to the kitchen.
comment: To use the elevator you must ask an employee for access.Dining hall hours:M-F7:30-9:30 AM11:15 AM-1:30 PM4:45-7:00 PMSS10:30 AM -12:30 PM5:00-6:30pm

name: Scripps College Garrison outside
directions: To the east of the main building of the performing arts center, just north of the music library.
comment: Bathrooms are single occupancy, lock to the outside.

name: Scripps College Denison Library NW side
directions: Enter library, cross courtyard, continue through past the desk, and the bathroom is on the left side

name: Scripps College Balch Hall
directions: From the southern Balch courtyard on the SW side take the elevator up to the 3rd floor. Take a left out of the elevator and the bathroom is on the left.

name: Scripps College Denison Library
directions: Enter library, walk past the front desk to the W side of the building, take a left around the corner and the bathroom is on the left.
comment: Not accessible

name: Scripps College Balch Auditorium
directions: Facing the entrance to Balch auditorium, turn left and follow the path around the building (there are signs to the bathroom). At the end of the hall, enter the building, and the bathrooms are immediately to the left

name: Smith Campus Center, Pomona College
directions: The bathroom is in the east wing of the basement, behind Doms lounge. It is marked unisex and accessible, single stall, and locking. It also seems to serve as a janitor's closet.There is an elevator in the west end of the courtyard, near the Coop Store and the ATM. Take that to the lower level, cut across the theater, and head east until you arrive at the bathroom.There is also ramp access on the south side of the building when Doms lounge is open for events.
comment: Building is open (at least) 9-5 M-F when school is in session.

name: Bernard Hall, Pitzer College
directions: The bathroom is on the 2nd floor, on the east side of the building. It is gender neutral, single stall, and locking. Elevator access is outside of the building, to the east, between Bernard Hall and Broad Center.
comment: Building is open (at least) 9-5 M-F when school is in session.

name: Scott Hall, Pitzer College
directions: There are two nearly identical single stall locking bathrooms, one on 1st floor one on the second. Both are on the far south side of the building.The bathroom on the first floor is marked as unisex, and accessible, though it does not meet ADA requirements. The door frame is too narrow (only 27') among other problems. There is elevator access to the east of the building, between the Broad and Bernard Hall.
comment: The building should be open (at least) 9-5 M-F when school is in session.

name: Roberts Hall South, Claremont McKenna College
directions: There is an elevator in the west end of the building. There are 2 bathrooms on the 2nd floor, one in the southwest corner, and one in the northwest corner. Both are single stall, and locking.
comment: Building should be open (at least) 9-5 M-F when school is in session.

name: Heggblade Center, Claremont McKenna College
directions: There are two single stall, locking, unisex bathrooms on an internal corridor on the 1st floor.
comment: Building is open (at least) 9-5 M-F, when school is in session.

name: Yogo Bliss
comment: hours: sun-th 11-11, f-s 11am-2am

name: Undergraduate Library
directions: two unisex bathrooms on the 4th floor. exit the elevator & head right.
comment: hours: m-th 8pm-5am, s-s 10am-5am,
